==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Preoccupy
<hw>Pre*oc"cu*py</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Preoccupied</conjf> <pr>(-p⟦imac⟧d)</pr>; <pos>p.
pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Preoccupying</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>pr⟦eacute⟧occuper</ets>. See <er>Preoccupate</er>,
<er>Occupy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To take possession of before
another; <as>as, to <ex>preoccupy</ex> a country not before
held</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To prepossess; to engage, occupy, or engross the
attention of, beforehand; hence, to prejudice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I Think it more respectful to the reader to leave something to
reflections than to <qex>preoccupy</qex> his judgment.</q>
<rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preocular</ent>⟦br⟧
